title: Yodahe Mulugeta’s CV
text:
My linkedin page | My github page






GPA - 3.95
Emphasis in Functional Programming
Computer Science social media President | BYU-I Computing Society
Computer Science Society Secretary | BYU-I Computing Society
Brigham Young University - Idaho Scholarship








Provided guidance to students in computer science, emphasizing beginning Python and SQL, fostering enhanced proficiency and understanding of fundamental concepts in programming
Directed students in addressing and resolving technical challenges, leading to a 15% increase in overall grades
Clarified technical concepts weekly for over 10 students with diverse experience levels





Designed visually captivating flyers for weekly Computing Society activities, incorporating event details, resulting in a 20% increase in event attendance
Executed a comprehensive communication strategy by distributing flyers, emailing event announcements, and promoting on social media platforms resulting in a 30% increase in audience reach and awareness of Computing Society events





Developed tailored meeting agendas for the Computing Society, outlining specific discussion topics, deadlines, and assigned responsibilities for each member of presidency
Assigned clear tasks to each member of the Computing Society presidency following meetings, ensuring accountability and progress on key action items






Programming Languages: Python, C#, MySQL
Tools: Git, GitHub, visual studio, vs code
Soft skills: Teamwork, Critical Thinking, Problem solvin
